Event posted: Contributing to R Meetup

text.text:
We will go through one or more of the bugs from Practicum 2 of the Contributing to R workshop materials, working in small groups. The objective is to find the root of the bug and consider how it might be fixed.

We will go through the bugs in the order presented over the series of meetups; since the bugs are independent you can attend as many meetups as you like!

The bug examples are from R 3.3.2. Participants are recommended to install R 3.3.2 before the meetup, as described in the workshop materials: <https://github.com/gmbecker/contributing_to_r_lesson>.

If you did not attend the Contributing to R workshop at useR!, you are recommended to read through the slides (outline.pdf) or watch the tutorial recording (soon to be published) and attempt the first exercise ("Code Analysis Practicum").

However, it is also possible to attend and work with others who have R 3.3.2 setup, as a stand-alone exercise.
